Academic, Account, and Financial Aid Information
Module 4: Customer Service Scripts and Scenarios
A mom of an enrolled student contacts Buckeye Link. She has questions about her son’s account, but she is not listed on the Student Information Release.
Hello, I want to mail a check to pay for the Autumn 2020 semester for my son. What is the balance on his account?

After reviewing your son’s account, I found that he has not listed you on his Student Information Release. While I am unable to share with you any balance that may be due, I will provide you with information on how students can find their Statement of Account online. Additionally, I will email your student to provide information on any balance that may be due.
Okay, that sounds great. I will make sure I am added to the release before I contact you the next time. Thanks!

When individuals are not authorized for information, there are a few things we can say to either address the unauthorized request or assist in general terms. Whenever possible, do your best to answer the question in general terms without providing information specific to the student.
In addition to providing general information, our service expectation is that you follow up with the student to provide them with the requested account information. In the email you should provide instructions on completing the Student Information Release. To make this process easier, there is an Email Template in Salesforce for you to use.
